verbose_text: The focus of the present study was CYP2C8 and its capacity to elucidate how the arachidonic acid metabolites, EETs, attenuate TNF-alpha induced inflammation through ROS in vascular endothelial cells and macrophages and improve endothelial function and provide new insight into how CYP2C8 derived EETs ameliorate vascular inflammatory diseases such as atherosclerosis.
